- `/predator lion orangutan` - Displays if the lion and orangutan are predators
- `/predator lion orangutan tiger` - Displays if the lion, orangutan and tiger are predators

# Part of Speech

The part of speech of a word or phrase is its function in a sentence. 

## Nouns

A noun is a person, place, thing, or idea. 

## Verbs

A verb is an action word.

## Adjectives

An adjective is a word that describes a noun or pronoun.

## Adverbs

An adverb is a word that describes a verb, adjective, or other adverb.

## Pronouns

A pronoun is a word that replaces a noun.

## Prepositions

A preposition is a word that shows a relationship between two words.

## Conjunctions

A conjunction is a word that connects two or more words, phrases, or clauses.

## Interjections

An interjection is a word or phrase that expresses emotion or surprise.

## Parts of a Sentence

A sentence has a subject, a predicate, and a complete thought.

## Subject

The subject of a sentence is what the sentence is about.

## Predicate

The predicate is the part of the sentence that tells what happens.

## Complete Thought

A complete thought is one that can stand alone.

## Sentence Types

Sentences can be simple or complex.

### Simple Sentence

A simple sentence has one independent clause.

### Complex Sentence

A complex sentence has one independent clause and one or more dependent clauses.

## Sentence Structure

Sentences can be in a simple or compound structure.

### Simple Sentence

A simple sentence has only one independent clause.

### Compound Sentence

A compound sentence has two or more independent clauses.

### Complex Sentence

A complex sentence has one independent clause and one or more dependent clauses.

## Types of Punctuation

Punctuation is the use of marks to show how a sentence should be read.

### Period

A period is a full stop at the end of a sentence.

The best way to ask a question is to follow these simple rules:

6. [Avoid asking for code](https://stackoverflow.com/help/on-topic). Instead, provide a [minimal reproducible example](https://stackoverflow.com/help/minimal-reproducible-example) of your issue.

10. [Follow up](https://stackoverflow.com/help/privileges/comment). If you need more help, you can follow up with the author of the answer or with other users in the comments.

### 1. Acknowledgements

This bot was built using the following tools:
* [DuckDuckGo API](https://duckduckgo.com/terms)

### 2. Requirements

* [Node.js](https://nodejs.org)
* [Yarn](https://yarnpkg.com)

### 3. Installation

```
git clone https://github.com/deligist/instructor.git
cd instructor
yarn install
yarn dev
```

### 4. Usage

##### Step 1

In the terminal, navigate to the root directory of the project.

##### Step 2

Execute the following command to start the bot:

```
yarn dev
```

##### Step 3

Once the bot is running, open your browser and navigate to `http://localhost:8080`.

This project was built by [Deligist](https://deligist.com).
